Introduce RegisterValue to hold either Constant or unparseable bytes

- rename `NonMandatoryRegisters:get` to `NonMandatoryRegisters::get_constant` and return `None` if the register value is unparseable;
- add `NonMandatoryRegisters:get` returning new `RegisterValue` holding either a `Constant` or unparseable bytes;

Close #611

Todo:
- [x] make `Tuple` type to encode tuples in JS (instead of `Set`);
- [x] implement the rest of the `SType` hierarchy;

Close #612

Todo:
- [x] remove `input_idx` and find input by box id;
- [x] clean up todo and commented code;

Close #594

Done:
- PBT to check that the target tokens count in box selection is not limited by max token per box limit;
- make `Tokens` in Wasm and C to be a wrapper around `Vec<Token>` not constrained by any limit;

Close #590 

Done in this PR:

- reproduce submitted in #590 code as JS test;
- reproduce the issue in Rust property-based test with various tokens count;
- fix the issue in the box selector and implement splitting the change into multiple boxes (see `make_change_boxes()`);
- add a guard that checks `selected inputs = target + change` for ERG and tokens at the end of the box selection process (see `check_input_preservation()`);
- refine `BoxSelectorError` for comprehensible error messages(remove generic error conversion in favor of tailored messages for each error case);

This PR implements JSON encoding for the hints type hierarchy, including `SigmaBoolean` and proof tree types used in sigma protocol. Besides that, it swaps the external `Scalar` with its wrapped version `Wscalar`.
To implement property-based testing all of the above-mentioned types got `Arbitrary` implementation.

